This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection and tracking in real-world traffic scenes. The use of state-of-the-art object detection and tracking methods also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The dataset used in the study is also likely to be of interest to researchers in robotics (cs.RO) as it can be used to evaluate the performance of tracking systems in autonomous vehicles. Finally, the rich annotations and video sequences in the dataset suggest a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) as well.
